dataIdInfo.idAbs: The dataset represents the admin level 2 boundaries of Sudan.

Consts.useLimit: See the COD/FOD Registry Terms of Use. This does not replace any terms of use information provided with the dataset.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from an email sent by the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. The geometry was updated by cleaning its attributes and topology. The layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS:
1. Created and populated admin 0 pcode field. Admin 0 p-code is "SD". 2. Created and populated admin 0 name field. Admin 0 name is "Sudan". 3. Created and populated a reference name field. 4. Two records existed for admin 2 unit "El Radoom". Record with OBJECTID "157" was removed, leaving record "163" with the same geometry and attribution. 5. Admin 2 unit "Geissan" had its small multipart poygon error removed 6. Admin 2 unit "Umm Dukhun" was given admin 1 p-code "SD06" to match its admin 1 name "Central Darfur". Its admin 2 p-code was changed to "SD06135", which comes from the shapefile "Sud_Settlementp_2015_wgs84" (The current admin 2 layer has recently had its p-codes syncronized with "Sud_Settlementp_2015_wgs84". Umm Dukhun's p-code changes have been made to further synchronize p-codes and corrects the inconsistent admin 1 name and p-code attribution). 7. Admin 1 name changed from "Al Gezira" to "El Gezira" to match spelling in Admin1. 8. Fixed 464 gap errors and 459 overlap errors in geometry.
The following comes from the COD Registry splash page for SUDAN: Admin Level 2 Boundaries:
"Disclaimer:
North Darfur state:
Locality boundaries - 13 from Census 2009 Tawilla, Kornoi, Alliet, Um Baro localities - Digitised by CRMA UNDP from the locality formation documents (2011) shared by the Bureau of Local Governance and the Secretariat of State Governance in El Fasher. The documents had hand drawn approximated maps and a settlement list. State boundary - Census 2009
South and East Darfur states:
Locality boundaries - Digitised by CRMA UNDP from the locality formation documents (2011) shared by the State Ministry of Local Governance in Nyala. Most of the documents had hand drawn maps and a settlement list. After digitisation, the boundaries were visually verified by the Ministry officials. State boundary - The Government of Sudan website shows the state boundary divisions with respect to the localities. http://www.sudan.gov.sd/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1006:east-darfur-state-&catid=43:2008-06-06-15-24-59&Itemid=71 The boundary between South and East Darfur states has been demarcated based on the locality boundaries.
West and Central Darfur states:
Locality boundaries - 13 from Census 2009 Jebel Moon, Forobaranga, Bindisi localities - from locality level CRMA workshops 2011 and visually verified by the State Ministry of Physical Planning in El Geneina. State boundary - The Government of Sudan website shows the state boundary divisions with respect to the localities. http://www.sudan.gov.sd/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1005:central-darfur-state-&catid=43:2008-06-06-15-24-59&Itemid=71 The boundary between West and Central Darfur states has been demarcated based on the locality boundaries and confirmed by the State Department for Planning in El Geneina.
Please be aware that these boundaries are not field verified and constantly being updated. They are not necessarily undisputed.
Most Recent Changes: The localities are adjusted to match the state boundaries."
